+{"type":"message","id":"ca3054d2","parentId":"df52512a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:29:53.105Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plan overview:\n{\n  \"goal\": \"Build the Weekly Commit Module v1 — a production micro-frontend (TypeScript/React) with Java 21 modular-monolith backend replacing 15Five for weekly planning. Implements structured weekly commitments with RCDO strategy linkage, chess-layer prioritization, lock/reconcile lifecycle with immutable snapshots, explicit carry-forward with provenance, native tickets with status workflow, manager team dashboard with exception review, conservative explainable AI assistance, rules-based notifications, derived read models for reporting, and comprehensive audit logging. Delivered as a route-level Module Federation remote integrated into the PA host app. Note: The PRD recommends Java 21 (§22) and all checks are npm-based; the monorepo root package.json orchestrates both the TypeScript frontend (Vite/React) and Java backend (Gradle) via shell-out scripts. SQL migrations use Flyway against PostgreSQL.\",\n  \"totalSteps\": 20,\n  \"stepTitles\": [\n    \"1. Monorepo scaffolding and build infrastructure\",\n    \"2. Domain model types, enums, and database schema\",\n    \"3. RCDO hierarchy management API\",\n    \"4. Weekly plan creation and commit CRUD API\",\n    \"5. Lock lifecycle and baseline snapshot API\",\n    \"6. Post-lock scope change and reconciliation API\",\n    \"7. Carry-forward and ticket/work item API\",\n    \"8. Team weekly view, manager review, and permissions API\",\n    \"9. Frontend micro-frontend setup and routing\",\n    \"10. RCDO management UI\",\n    \"11. My Week page with commit list and capacity meter\",\n    \"12. Lock flow and reconcile view UI\",\n    \"13. Team Week dashboard UI\",\n    \"14. Tickets UI and search/filter/history views\",\n    \"15. Notifications backend and frontend panel\",\n    \"16. AI provider abstraction and commit assistance\",\n    \"17. AI risk detection and reconciliation assistance\",\n    \"18. Derived read models and operational reporting\",\n    \"19. Configuration management and admin settings\",\n    \"20. Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\"\n  ]\n}\n\nStep 11: My Week page with commit list and capacity meter\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-11\",\n  \"title\": \"My Week page with commit list and capacity meter\",\n  \"description\": \"Build the My Week page per PRD §10 (My Week surface) and §13 FR-2.\\n\\n**MyWeekPage component:**\\n- Displays current week plan or upcoming draft (auto-selects based on lifecycle stage).\\n- Week selector to navigate between weeks.\\n- Plan state badge (DRAFT, LOCKED, RECONCILING, RECONCILED) with compliance indicator.\\n- Lock/Reconcile action buttons (contextual based on plan state).\\n\\n**CommitList component:**\\n- Ordered list of commits showing: priority rank, chess piece icon, title, RCDO path, estimate points, linked ticket key, status.\\n- Drag-and-drop reorder using a library (e.g., @dnd-kit/sortable). Keyboard-accessible reorder alternative: move-up/move-down buttons per commit (WCAG 2.1 AA).\\n- Inline expand to show description, success criteria, provenance info if carried forward.\\n- Edit and delete actions per commit (only in DRAFT state).\\n\\n**CommitForm component (modal or panel):**\\n- Fields: title (required), description (textarea), chess piece (radio/select with piece icons and descriptions), estimate points (segmented control: 1/2/3/5/8), primary RCDO link (hierarchical selector using RcdoTreeView in picker mode), success criteria (textarea, required badge for King/Queen), linked ticket (search/select).\\n- Real-time validation: required fields highlighted, chess piece limits checked (show 'Max 1 King already used' warning), RCDO linkage rules enforced.\\n- Carry-forward provenance banner if commit was carried forward (shows source week and streak count).\\n\\n**CapacityMeter component:**\\n- Visual bar/gauge showing committed points vs weekly budget (default 10).\\n- Color-coded: green (under budget), yellow (near budget), red (over budget).\\n- Breakdown by chess piece type.\\n- Override indicator if manager has set custom capacity.\\n\\n**Soft warnings panel:**\\n- Warning if >8 active commits in the plan.\\n- Warning if >40% of total points are Pawn commits.\\n- These are UI warnings only, not lock blockers.\\n\\n**Component tests:** commit list renders in priority order, drag-drop reorder updates priority, commit form validates all required fields, chess piece limit enforced in UI, capacity meter shows correct totals, soft warnings appear at thresholds, RCDO selector enforces linkage rules, keyboard reorder works.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nThis is relay round 2. Another agent has already worked on this step.\n\nYou are in VERIFICATION MODE. Your default action is to APPROVE.\nFocus your review on the DIFF — the changes made in the previous round.\nOnly make changes if there is a MATERIAL defect: failing check, missing step requirement, logic bug, or security issue.\nStyle preferences, alternative approaches, comment wording, and optional polish are NOT grounds for changes.\n\nIf all checks pass and the step requirements are met, approve immediately.\nLog anything else you notice as observations — do not act on them.\n\nPrevious agent's notes:\nAll checks pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## What was built\n\n### API Layer\n- **`planTypes.ts`**: TypeScript types mirroring the Java backend DTOs (`PlanResponse`, `CommitResponse`, `PlanWithCommitsResponse`, `CreateCommitPayload`, `UpdateCommitPayload`)\n- **`planApi.ts`**: API functions for all plan/commit operations (get-or-create plan, create/update/delete commit, reorder, lock)\n- **`planHooks.ts`**: React hooks (`usePlanApi`, `useCurrentPlan`) following the same pattern as `rcdoHooks.ts`\n\n### Components (`/components/myweek/`)\n- **`CapacityMeter.tsx`**: Visual bar/gauge with green/yellow/red color coding, per-chess-piece breakdown, manager override badge\n- **`SoftWarningsPanel.tsx`**: Warns when >8 active commits or >40% pawn points (UI-only, not lock blockers)\n- **`CommitForm.tsx`**: Full modal form with all required fields — title (required), description, chess piece radio with icons/descriptions and limit enforcement (Max 1 King, Max 2 Queens), estimate points segmented control (1/2/3/5/8), RCDO hierarchical picker using `RcdoTreeView`, success criteria (required for King/Queen), linked ticket; carry-forward provenance banner\n- **`CommitList.tsx`**: Ordered list with DnD reorder (`@dnd-kit/sortable`), move-up/down keyboard buttons (WCAG 2.1 AA), inline expand with description/success criteria/provenance, edit/delete actions (DRAFT-only)\n\n### Page\n- **`MyWeek.tsx`**: Full implementation with week selector (prev/next/today), plan state badge (DRAFT/LOCKED/RECONCILING/RECONCILED), compliance indicator, lock button (DRAFT only), reconcile hint (LOCKED/RECONCILING), capacity meter, soft warnings, commit list, CommitForm modal, delete confirm dialog\n\n### Tests (204 total, all passing)\n- **`CommitList.test.tsx`** (29 tests): Priority order rendering, keyboard reorder, inline expand, state-based button visibility\n- **`CommitForm.test.tsx`** (31 tests): Required field validation, chess piece limit enforcement, estimate points, RCDO picker, carry-forward banner, submission\n- **`CapacityMeter.test.tsx`** (16 tests): Totals display, color coding, breakdown by piece, override badge\n- **`MyWeekPage.test.tsx`** (27 tests): Week navigation, plan state badge, lock button, soft warnings at thresholds, capacity meter\n\nVerdict: changes_made\n\n```observations\n- [low] frontend/src/components/myweek/CommitList.tsx: The useEffect for syncing localCommits uses `incomingIdsKey` (sorted commit IDs) as dependency. After a server refetch following a reorder (same IDs, new priorityOrder values), the effect won't fire, so localCommits will preserve the optimistically reordered state. This is intentional but means if the server returns a different order than the optimistic one, the UI will be stale until the ID set changes.\n- [low] frontend/src/components/myweek/CommitForm.tsx: The linked ticket field accepts a free-text workItemId. In a future step (step 14, Tickets UI), this should be upgraded to a search/select picker backed by GET /api/tickets?teamId=...\n- [low] frontend/src/routes/MyWeek.tsx: The `buildRcdoLabels()` helper is called unconditionally on every render. Since it traverses the RCDO tree, it could be memoized with `useMemo` for performance with large trees (acceptable for v1).\n```\n\nPrior observations from earlier steps (address if they fall within this step's scope):\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 backend/build.gradle.kts: Uses Eclipse JDT formatter instead of google-java-format because google-java-format (and palantirJavaFormat) rely on `com.sun.tools.javac.util.Log$DeferredDiagnosticHandler.getDiagnostics()` which was removed in JDK 25. Future steps should be aware of this constraint; a switch to google-java-format would require either downgrading the JDK to ≤24 or waiting for a google-java-format release that supports JDK 25.\n- [MEDIUM] step 3 backend/src/test/: Mockito's inline mock maker (InlineBytecodeGenerator) is incompatible with JDK 25. Switched to subclass mock maker via the extensions file. This means final classes/methods cannot be mocked in tests — not an issue for our service classes but worth noting for future steps.\n- [MEDIUM] step 3 backend/src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker: Set to `mock-maker-subclass` to work around Mockito inline-mock-maker incompatibility with JDK 25. This means final classes/methods cannot be mocked in tests. Not an issue today, but future steps adding mocks of final types will need to handle this.\n- [MEDIUM] step 5 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/lock/service/LockService.java: Auto-lock idempotency is implemented for repeat calls, but the step also called for optimistic locking or compare-and-swap to protect concurrent runners. I did not see explicit concurrency protection beyond state checks.\n- [MEDIUM] step 5 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/lock/service/LockService.java: Auto-lock idempotency relies only on a state check (DRAFT guard). There is no database-level optimistic lock (`@Version`) to protect against concurrent auto-lock runners. This is acceptable for v1 given single-instance deployment, but a future step should add `@Version` to `WeeklyPlan` and a Flyway migration for the `version` column if concurrent scheduling ever becomes a concern.\n- [MEDIUM] step 6 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/reconcile/service/ReconciliationService.java: The `getReconciliationView` method allows state RECONCILING or RECONCILED, but `setCommitOutcome` only allows RECONCILING. If a manager views a RECONCILED plan via `getReconciliationView`, then tries to `setCommitOutcome`, they get a 400. This is correct behavior but worth documenting clearly in the API.\n- [MEDIUM] step 6 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/reconcile/service/ScopeChangeService.java: The `removePostLockCommit` method sets `outcome = CANCELED` immediately (pre-reconciliation). During `submitReconciliation`, this commit is treated as already having an outcome (CANCELED), which is correct. However, calling `setCommitOutcome` on an already-CANCELED (removed) commit during RECONCILING would allow overriding the post-lock cancellation — a guard could prevent this in a future step.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: Peer visibility is filtered at the field level (PeerCommitView strips sensitive fields) but the \"current and next week only\" temporal constraint for peer callers is not enforced at the service layer — a peer can request any historical week. Not a breaking issue for v1 but worth tightening in a future step.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: `checkCanAccessTeam` requires the caller to be a team member. An ADMIN-managed parent team manager without explicit membership in a child team would be blocked from viewing that child team's data. This is consistent with current behavior but the \"indirect reports' aggregates\" capability from the step spec is not fully exercised in the team-week endpoint.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: Peer visibility appears field-filtered, but the “current and next week only” peer time-window rule may not be enforced server-side for arbitrary requested weeks.\n\nFiles changed so far:\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/cost.json\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/observations.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/sessions/continuous/relay-a/2026-03-24T04-23-35-130Z_4c4202d2-9023-459a-b908-dfaede19919d.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/state.json\nfrontend/package.json\nfrontend/src/routes/MyWeek.tsx\npackage-lock.json\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/steps/11\nfrontend/src/__tests__/CapacityMeter.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__tests__/CommitForm.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__tests__/CommitList.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__tests__/MyWeekPage.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/api/planApi.ts\nfrontend/src/api/planHooks.ts\nfrontend/src/api/planTypes.ts\nfrontend/src/components/myweek\n\nWhen done, explain what you reviewed, what you changed (if anything), and your assessment.\n\nEnd with:\nVerdict: approve  — if the step is complete and correct, no more changes needed\nVerdict: changes_made  — if you made fixes or improvements\nVerdict: replan_needed  — if the step is structurally impossible to complete as planned and needs controller-managed replanning"}],"timestamp":1774337393104}}
